headline: 3 Absurdly Cheap Growth Stocks to Load Up On Right Now
summary: Novo Nordisk, PayPal, and Dell Technologies are modestly priced growth stocks with a lot of potential to rise higher.  Buying stocks that are trading at cheap valuations can set you up for some big gains later on.  Although many stocks look expensive today, there are three growth stocks which still seem absurdly cheap right now: Novo Nordisk (NYSE: NVO), PayPal (NASDAQ: PYPL), and Dell Technologies (NYSE: DELL).

headline: 1 Beaten-Down Growth Stock Down 76% to Buy Right Now
summary: PayPal's stock has plummeted 76% from its all-time high of $310.  With a 71% penetration rate in the U.S. payment app market, PayPal is a leading choice for digital payments.  CEO Alex Chriss is shifting the focus from just payments to a broader commerce platform and reducing checkout times by 32%.
